it all remarkably well.</p><p>Its quite simple you make content, we put it in front of the right peoples smiling faces, and we both reap the benefits.</p><p> </p><p>Here is one way to think about it:</p><p>Imagine your new Frankenstein cyborg creation is ready and its great, you are selling them to a few people out of your garage and you are getting by but you don\'t really have the time or even will to do anything but <strong>create</strong> and improve them.</p><p>That\'s where I come in.... so I build you a fancy store to sell them in and it all looks great, that\'s <strong>development.</strong></p><p>We talk some more and while you like the store you would like it more if people were actually in it....</p><p>So I create an event at The Festival which will demonstrate your Creation\'s cool abilities and I paint a sign saying ‘The Creation Demonstration coming to The Festival, Friday’, that’s <strong>advertising</strong>.</p><p>If you make an army of Scaled Down Abominable Creations and we walk them into town as they carry that sign, that’s <strong>promotion</strong>.</p><p>If the army gets hacked, starts taking over the world, and The Daily Show writes a story about it, that’s <strong>publicity</strong>.</p><p>And if I get the world to then laugh about it, that’s <strong>public relations</strong>.</p><p>If the town’s citizens go to see your creation, I show them the many ways it can entertain them, explain how much fun they’ll have spending money on one, answer their questions and ultimately, they buy a lot at the event, that’s <strong>sales</strong>.</p><p>And if I planned this whole thing, that’s <strong>marketing.</strong></p><p> </p><p>Chances are your situation is not quite as elaborate, but this is the secret to your success and what we do in a nutshell. The only difference is we do this all online, which is called <strong>web development and marketing</strong>.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p>So you want to take your business to the next level?  I\'ve been there!  I