happen to your asset if one or both of those freelancers moved, would you still get post project support for your asset? Anyway, among freelancers we are the most affordable because jobs aren\'t as unreliable. And don\'t even get me started with a corporation on this project unless you want to be paying for the entire scrum management team and their pensions. Talk about overhead. Not to mention they might treat you like a number.  They might wonder why you are coming to them with such a dinky project.</h3><h3>You get the benefits of hiring a large businesses as well as all of the benefits of hiring a freelancer,  with none of the negatives.   We have a name to uphold its called accountability</h3><h3>So this is what really sets us apart.  Why isn\'t anyone else doing this? Putting together a team of free lancers.  Well, collaboration has never been so easy.  Flower City Online has created a seamless workflow, making it possible for us if we wanted to have 14 people on a job each putting in an hour a day and sending it to the master.</h3><h3>Again, we promise we won\'t quote you a price unless it is a win-win for both of us.  Our goal is to earn your business for the long term.  So send us your thoughts today if you think we can work together to grow your business.</h3><h3> </h3><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><h3>You don\'t see many of these teams because corporations are safe and cushy and offer many benefits and would steal freelancers away too quickly... but this is changing.  Even some of our developers are working full time and contribute when they can, but that is a busy life style with a family.  No, but most of our developers have been working for us since they first became what the corporate world would call junior developers.  Because of this experience they know so much more than software development.  Going to the 9-5 and just coding would get boring.  We sacrifice full time benefits though.  Our loss your gain.</h3><p> </p></div></div></div><div id=\"panel-87-5