bullish on the economy and the outlook for their sales growth in the next year, but just 27 percent say they plan to hire full-time staff, according to the <a href=\"https://www.cnbc.com/cnbc-survey-monkey-small-business-survey/\">CNBC/SurveyMonkey Small Business Survey</a>.\r\n\r\nFreelance staffing could bridge this gap, especially as the Trump administration expands the definition of the freelance labor market. Earlier this month, Labor Secretary Alexander Acosta withdrew an Obama-era legal opinion that favored a broad definition of who is an employee versus who is a freelancer. The move allows companies to classify more workers as freelancers, meaning they are not subject to the same federal wage and hour regulations as salaried employees.\r\n\r\nThe freelance economy is booming. According to 2016 data from the <a href=\"https://www.cnbc.com/2016/10/13/gig-economy-is-growing-heres-how-much.html\">Metropolitan Policy Program at the Brookings Institution</a>, the number of workers operating as independent contractors has increased by 27 percent more than payroll employees.\r\n<div id=\"inline_movable_ad\"></div>\r\nBut businesses on Main Street have been reluctant to embrace this growing, often inexpensive and flexible labor pool. Out of more than 2,200 small-business owners recently surveyed by <a class=\"inline_asset\" title=\"https://www.manta.com/\" href=\"https://www.manta.com/\">Manta</a>, only 36 percent currently use contract workers. Eighty-five percent, meanwhile, said that they have no intentions of hiring any contract workers this year. The reasons for this hiring reluctance range from general employer-staff relationship fears to legal and compliance worries.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"group-container \">\r\n<div class=\"inline-player\">\r\n<div class=\"pro-video-chapters fall\"></div>\r\n<div id=\"player_1_104559744_1\" class=\"asset cnbcvideo imgasset desc_size600_400 featuredPromo\" data-dockable=\"1\">\r\n\r\n<span class=\"video-icon\"><a class=\"\" href=\"https://www.cnbc.com/video/2017/07/05/paychex-small-business-jobs-index-down-for-4th-consecutive-month.html\" data-videoid=\"3000633259\" data-videotype=\"\"><img title=\"Paychex small business jobs index down for 4th consecutive month\" src=\"https://fm.cnbc.com/applications/cnbc.com/resources/img/editorial/2017/07/05/104567889-4ED2-SB-0705-SmallBiz.600x400.jpg?v=1499255144\" alt=\"Small business jobs index down for 4th consecutive month\" width=\"600\" height=\"400\" /></a></span>\r\n<div class=\"headline\">Paychex small business jobs index down for 4th consecutive month</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"group\">\r\n\r\nAaron Lin, managing director of a small web design and digital marketing agency, cites the inability to monitor freelancers as one reason he\'s hesitant to outsource important tasks. Lin prefers the reliability of traditional employees, knowing they will treat his business information with care and represent his company in a professional manner.\r\n<div id=\"dart_wrapper_responsiverectangle\" class=\"dart_wrapper dart_ads_noniframe_responsiverectangle badge-ad\"></div>\r\nJesse Harrison, founder of Zeus Legal Funding in Los Angeles, worries more about compliance and security issues.\r\n\r\n\"When things are getting done at a remote location by a freelancer who is not associated with your company, there are a lot of legal issues there,\" Harrison said. \"If the freelancer\'s computer gets hacked and your client\'s information gets into the wrong hands, you would be responsible.\"\r\n\r\nConcerns like these, while valid, may also be overstated, as staffing companies ride the freelance economy boom and cover some of these headaches.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"group-container last\">\r\n<blockquote class=\"embed-container pull-quote\"><span class=\"quote\">\"IN MANY INSTANCES, FREELANCERS ARE GOING TO BE MORE INVESTED IN THE OUTCOME OF THEIR WORK FOR YOU THAN ARE W-2 EMPLOYEES.\"</span><span class=\"author\">-Amber Hinds, owner of digital agency Road Warrior Creative</span></blockquote>\r\n<div class=\"group\">\r\n\r\nUpwork, the world\'s largest global freelancing platform, with 3 million jobs posted annually, vets its talent and offers a <a class=\"inline_asset\" href=\"https://www.upwork.com/enterprise/\">premium solution for enterprise</a> that ensures worker classification and onboarding requirements are met. For clients that subscribe to its compliance services, Upwork can also receive indemnification from misclassification risk, which can lead to an IRS audit.\r\n\r\nSmall-business owners who do use freelancers say there are a few practical considerations to keep in mind in order to maximize use of this labor market alternative and minimize the expense.\r\n\r\n<b><strong>More from the CNBC/SurveyMonkey Small Business Survey:\r\n</strong></b><a href=\"https://www.cnbc.com/2017/06/14/tech-help-wanted-about-half-of-small-businesses-dont-have-a-website.html\">Why half of small businesses still don\'t have a website</a>\r\n<a href=\"https://www.cnbc.com/2017/06/09/why-small-business-can-love-trump-but-still-not-create-many-jobs.html\">They may be optimistic, but small-business owners just aren\'t hiring</a>\r\n<a href=\"https://www.cnbc.com/2017/06/26/2-big-trump-promises-republican-voters-wont-judge-him-on.html\">Entrepreneurs really don\'t care what Trump does on trade and immigration</a>\r\n\r\n\"I don\'t think that small-business owners should let fears of business reputation or security stop them from working with freelancers,\" said Amber Hinds, owner of digital agency <a class=\"inline_asset\" href=\"https://roadwarriorcreative.com/\">Road Warrior Creative</a>. \"In many instances, freelancers are going to be <em>more</em> invested in the outcome of their work for you than are W-2 employees. If they don\'t produce good results for you, you have more recourse with freelancers than you do with an employee,\" Hinds said.\r\n\r\nShe said business owners can sue, report them to the Better Business Bureau or write negative reviews of freelancers online. \"I think most freelancers are aware of this and will strive to provide great results because of it,\" Hinds said.\r\n\r\nJonathan Weber, CEO of tech publishing company <a class=\"inline_asset\" href=\"https://www.marathon-studios.com/\">Marathon Studios, </a>said it\'s fair to have trust and security concerns. \"Most people who consistently use freelancers have been burned at some point,\" he said. But Weber added that the benefits still outweigh the risks: Most freelancers are highly skilled professionals who can bring value to a company at an affordable cost.\r\n\r\n\"To identify the best freelancers, my strategy has always been to hire multiple contractors to work on portions of a single project and then retain the ones who prove themselves to be the best workers,\" Weber said.\r\n\r\nHe added, \"As time goes on, you start to build relationships with a network of individuals who you have worked with before, and will be able to directly approach them with work without having to face the uncertainty and risk of hiring someone new.\"\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>','Small-business owners don\'t like to use freelance workers. Are they wrong?','','inherit','closed','closed','','450-revision-v1','','','2017-08-05 05:10:20','2017-08-05 05:10:20','',450,'http://www.localhost/fco/450-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(465,1,'2017-08-05 06:09:20','2017-08-05 06:09:20','<div id=\"pl-465\"  class=\"panel-layout\" ><div id=\"pg-465-0\"  class=\"panel-grid panel-has-style\"  data-style=\"{&quot;row_stretch&quot;:&quot;full&quot;,&quot;cell_alignment&quot;:&quot;flex-start&quot;,&quot;align&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;overlay&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;overlay_color&quot;:&quot;#000000&quot;}\" ><div class=\"siteorigin-panels-stretch panel-row-style panel-row-style-for-465-0\" style=\"padding: 100px 0; \" data-stretch-type=\"full\" data-overlay=\"true\" data-overlay-color=\"#000000\" ><div id=\"pgc-465-0-0\"  class=\"panel-grid-cell\"  data-weight=\"1\" ><div id=\"panel-465-0-0-0\" class=\"so-panel widget widget_sow-editor panel-first-child panel-last-child\" data-index=\"0\" data-style=\"{&quot;background_image_attachment&quot;:false,&quot;background_display&quot;:&quot;tile&quot;,&quot;content_alignment&quot;:&quot;left&quot;,&quot;title_color&quot;:&quot;#443f3f&quot;,&quot;headings_color&quot;:&quot;#443f3f&quot;}\" ><div style=\"text-align: left;\" data-title-color=\"#443f3f\" data-headings-color=\"#443f3f\" class=\"panel-widget-style panel-widget-style-for-465-0-0-0\" ><div class=\"so-widget-sow-editor so-widget-sow-editor-base\">\n<div class=\"siteorigin-widget-tinymce textwidget\">\n	<div id=\"pg-3543-1\" class=\"panel-grid ppb-row\">\n<div class=\"ppb-row panel-row-style panel-row-style- ppb-stretch-full-width\">\n<div class=\"panel-grid-cell-container\">\n<div id=\"pgc-3543-1-1\" class=\"ppb-col panel-grid-cell \">\n<div id=\"panel-3543-1-1-0\" class=\"ppb-block\">\n<p>Hi I am Nicholas Vaughn and I would love to introduce my team of talents. We have many talents on tap here at Flower City Online.  I feel we are all well versed so it is hard to relegate one person to any one position.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p> </p>\n<p> </p>\n<div id=\"pg-3543-1\" class=\"panel-grid ppb-row\">\n<div class=\"ppb-row panel-row-style panel-row-style- ppb-stretch-full-width\">\n<div class=\"panel-grid-cell-container\">\n<div id=\"pgc-3543-1-1\" class=\"ppb-col panel-grid-cell \">\n<p><strong>A little about how and why we are here....</strong></p>\n<div id=\"panel-3543-1-1-0\" class=\"ppb-block\">\n<p>We are a few maverick freelancers who seized the opportunity to start a business and help out friends in the same situation. From this beginning we’ve harnessed the vigor of the small business owner and banded with them to increase value and produce better brands by expanding their online presence. Our clients all have one thing in common, they are creators of extraordinary things. They have another thing in common though and that is that they lack the time to do all the other important parts of business. We are your other half! The creators need to keep creating. They cannot be bogged down with learning and then actually implementing what we do.</p>\n<p>We do website operations and content marketing. This is THE BARE MINIMUM. We keep expenses low! We go in and once we have made sure you have found your sweet spot and identified your content tilt, we build you the platform.  When you have your cult following, then we setup your new enterprise.</p>\n<p>For your platform to work beyond a hobby based business, scalability is key. That means you need a team to get you to the next level.</p>\n<p> </p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p><strong>A few basic roles in Web Development are:</strong></p>\n<p>Front end developer</p>\n<p>Back end developer</p>\n<p>Dev Ops</p>\n<p>Software Tester</p>\n<p>Project Manager</p>\n<p> </p>\n<div id=\"pg-3543-1\" class=\"panel-grid ppb-row\">\n<div class=\"ppb-row panel-row-style panel-row-style- ppb-stretch-full-width\">\n<div class=\"panel-grid-cell-container\">\n<div id=\"pgc-3543-1-1\" class=\"ppb-col panel-grid-cell \">\n<div id=\"panel-3543-1-1-0\" class=\"ppb-block\">\n<p><strong>The few basic roles in marketing are:</strong></p>\n<p>CCO Chief content officer (founder) this person is responsible for setting the overall editorial and content mission statement. Its many peoples responsibility to create content but it’s the CCOs responsibility that the ‘stories’ remain consistent and makes sense to the audience. In addition, the CCO must understand how the stories translate into results that address the organizations business issues, get new subscribers, keep subscribers, etc.. ;</p>\n<p>managing editor half storyteller half project manager, the ME executes the project plan on behalf of the CCO; whereas the cco focuses on strategy and some content, the managing editors job is all execution, working with the roles that well talk about in a little bit to make the content stories come alive, including scheduling the content.</p>\n<p>Chief listening officer, the role of the CLO is to function as air traffic control for social media and other content channels. This person is there to listen to the groups, maintain the conversation, and route and or notify feedback to other team members who can engage in appropriate conversations to you, to editorial, or perhaps to the sales team. This feedback mechanism is critical if the content is going to make a difference to your customers. The CLO must also monitor how the content is performing on all media sites, blogs and get that intelligence back to the ME.</p>\n<p>Director of audience, this person is charged with monitoring the members of your audience making sure all content creators are intamitely familiar with thei r characteristics their passion triggers and the direction you wan tthem to take. The DOA is also responsible for building assets like direct mail lists, direct email lists, and encryptions that can grow and be segmented as your content missions grows and expands.</p>\n<p>The channel master, wherever your content is headed social media, email, print, end user, the  CM is  responsible for getting the most and what works best on each channel. What works best on SlideShare? When should you send your reminder email newsletters and how frequently? Whats the proper ratio of owned versus curated content your business should distribute on twitter? Whos keeping track of mobile strategy and execution? Youchannel will look to this guy for answers.</p>\n<p>The Chief Technologist, as marketing information technology continues to merge there will be a need of at least one individual whos sole purpose is to leverage the proper use of these technologies into the content marketing process the person will be responsable for your publishing systems or the plumbing such as your website infrastructure and email systems and how they integrate together.</p>\n<p>The creative director, the desiugn and creative look to your content is more important thatn ever especially as creative and social channels become an increasingly important method of attracting and maintaining subscribers. The CD is responsible for the overall look and fell of all your content including your website your blog, images, photography, and every other piece of collateral you create.</p>\n<p>Influencer relations, the role formerly known as media relations will evolve into that a manager of influencers, this persons responsibilities include developing your hit list of influencers, maintaining your direct relationships with them, and integrating them into your marketing process in the most impactful ways. Freelancer and agency relations, as content demands continue to evolve and increase, your orgs relations with freelancers and other content venders will grow as well. The orgs need to cultivate their own expert teams and network and it is this persons job to negotiate rates and responsibilities are united in their work on behalf of your Content Inc. program.</p>\n<p>The Content curation director, as you begin to develop content assets you will have amazing opportunities to repackage and repurpose your content. But the role of the content manager is to look at all the assets being developed by the organization and strategize ways to create new pieces of content form them. This involves taking other people’s content, adding to it, enhancing it, and/or giving it a new context or perspective so that it evolves into a new piece of content. They are responsible for understanding the content assets available to work with including text image audio, effectively tagging, categorizing, and coordinating these materials into a data asset management system, working with the content marketing team on a clear channel plan, and developing and managing content marketing plan, developing and executing strategy by using existing resources.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p> </p>\n<p> </p>\n<p> </p>\n<p> </p>\n<p> </p>\n<p> </p>\n<div id=\"pg-3543-1\" class=\"panel-grid ppb-row\">\n<div class=\"ppb-row panel-row-style panel-row-style- ppb-stretch-full-width\">\n<div class=\"panel-grid-cell-container\">\n<div id=\"pgc-3543-1-1\" class=\"ppb-col panel-grid-cell \">\n<div id=\"panel-3543-1-1-0\" class=\"ppb-block\">\n<h2>Kevin Jones, The Founder</h2>\n<p>When I was young, I watched in awe as my father took an old MG sports car down to its frame, and then rebuilt the whole thing. I was hooked! I inherited his fascination for breaking things into their component parts. I love to figure out how things work, and then improve on the model to make it work better. And that’s exactly what I do at Ectobox.</p>\n<p>Meanwhile, my professional background in Accounting keeps me grounded. I know that at the end of the day, the numbers have to add up. To grow your business you need more money coming in than going out. Your time, your people’s time, and your systems are all valuable resources your control. No matter how strong your company’s revenues are, if you’re bleeding money from these areas, it’s a drag on profits. I’m passionate about building, and my favorite thing to do is build businesses. Just like you, I work hard to make sure my own company is efficient in our processes and our systems, so I can keep my overhead low. And I personally oversee every project to make sure the job gets done right. Like you, I don’t like to waste money. I like to get things done. Just ask our <a title=\"Clients\" href=\"http://www.ectobox.com/clients/\">clients</a>.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div id=\"pg-3543-2\" class=\"panel-grid ppb-row\">\n<div class=\"ppb-row panel-row-style panel-row-style- ppb-stretch-full-width\">\n<div class=\"panel-grid-cell-container\">\n<div id=\"pgc-3543-2-0\" class=\"ppb-col panel-grid-cell \"> </div>\n<div id=\"pgc-3543-2-1\" class=\"ppb-col panel-grid-cell \">\n<div id=\"panel-3543-2-1-0\" class=\"ppb-block\">\n<h2>OUR PROCESS</h2>\n</div>\n<div id=\"panel-3543-2-1-1\" class=\"ppb-block ppb-no-mobile-spacing\">\n<p>We take the builder\'s approach of \"measure twice, cut once\". That\'s how carpenters avoid costly mistakes, and it makes the same good sense in the world of custom software design.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div id=\"pg-3543-4\" class=\"panel-grid ppb-row\">\n<div class=\"ppb-row panel-row-style panel-row-style- ppb-stretch-full-width\">\n<div class=\"panel-grid-cell-container\">\n<div id=\"pgc-3543-4-0\" class=\"ppb-col panel-grid-cell \">\n<div id=\"panel-3543-4-0-0\" class=\"ppb-block\">\n<h2>OUR VALUES</h2>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div id=\"pg-3543-5\" class=\"panel-grid ppb-row\">\n<div class=\"ppb-row panel-row-style panel-row-style- ppb-stretch-full-width\">\n<div class=\"panel-grid-cell-container\">\n<div id=\"pgc-3543-5-0\" class=\"ppb-col panel-grid-cell \"> </div>\n<div id=\"pgc-3543-5-1\" class=\"ppb-col panel-grid-cell \">\n<div id=\"panel-3543-5-1-0\" class=\"ppb-block infobox_about\">\n<h2>WE ARE HONEST</h2>\n<div class=\"woo-sc-hr\"> </div>\n<ul>\n<li>We don’t sell what you don’t need.</li>\n<li>We won\'t lie to you.</li>\n<li>We guarantee a fit between the project and the team or we won\'t accept the work.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<div id=\"panel-3543-5-1-1\" class=\"ppb-block infobox_about\">\n<h2>WE ARE DEPENDABLE</h2>\n<div class=\"woo-sc-hr\"> </div>\n<ul>\n<li>We\'ll be there.</li>\n<li>We won\'t flake out on you.</li>\n<li>We will be available.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div id=\"pgc-3543-5-2\" class=\"ppb-col panel-grid-cell \">\n<div id=\"panel-3543-5-2-0\" class=\"ppb-block infobox_about\">\n<h2>WE WORK SMART</h2>\n<div class=\"woo-sc-hr\"> </div>\n<ul>\n<li>We define the real problem.</li>\n<li>We do the right work or we don’t do it at all.</li>\n<li>We believe in efficiency, no wasted time, money, or effort.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<div id=\"panel-3543-5-2-1