tag\">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;</span>\r\n\r\n		<span class=\"pun\">&lt;?</span><span class=\"pln\">php the_excerpt</span><span class=\"pun\">(</span><span class=\"pln\">__</span><span class=\"pun\">(</span><span class=\"str\">\'Continue reading »\'</span><span class=\"pun\">,</span><span class=\"str\">\'example\'</span><span class=\"pun\">));</span> <span class=\"pun\">?&gt;</span>\r\n\r\n            <span class=\"tag\">&lt;/div&gt;</span><span class=\"com\">&lt;!-- /#post-&lt;?php get_the_ID(); ?&gt; --&gt;</span>\r\n\r\n        <span class=\"pun\">&lt;?</span><span class=\"pln\">php endwhile</span><span class=\"pun\">;</span> <span class=\"pun\">?&gt;</span>\r\n\r\n		<span class=\"tag\">&lt;div</span> <span class=\"atn\">class</span><span class=\"pun\">=</span><span class=\"atv\">\"navigation\"</span><span class=\"tag\">&gt;</span>\r\n			<span class=\"tag\">&lt;span</span> <span class=\"atn\">class</span><span class=\"pun\">=</span><span class=\"atv\">\"newer\"</span><span class=\"tag\">&gt;</span><span class=\"pun\">&lt;?</span><span class=\"pln\">php previous_posts_link</span><span class=\"pun\">(</span><span class=\"pln\">__</span><span class=\"pun\">(</span><span class=\"str\">\'« Newer\'</span><span class=\"pun\">,</span><span class=\"str\">\'example\'</span><span class=\"pun\">))</span> <span class=\"pun\">?&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">&lt;/span&gt;</span> <span class=\"tag\">&lt;span</span> <span class=\"atn\">class</span><span class=\"pun\">=</span><span class=\"atv\">\"older\"</span><span class=\"tag\">&gt;</span><span class=\"pun\">&lt;?</span><span class=\"pln\">php next_posts_link</span><span class=\"pun\">(</span><span class=\"pln\">__</span><span class=\"pun\">(</span><span class=\"str\">\'Older »\'</span><span class=\"pun\">,</span><span class=\"str\">\'example\'</span><span class=\"pun\">))</span> <span class=\"pun\">?&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">&lt;/span&gt;</span>\r\n		<span class=\"tag\">&lt;/div&gt;</span><span class=\"com\">&lt;!-- /.navigation --&gt;</span>\r\n\r\n	<span class=\"pun\">&lt;?</span><span class=\"pln\">php </span><span class=\"kwd\">else</span><span class=\"pun\">:</span> <span class=\"pun\">?&gt;</span>\r\n\r\n		<span class=\"tag\">&lt;div</span> <span class=\"atn\">id</span><span class=\"pun\">=</span><span class=\"atv\">\"post-404\"</span> <span class=\"atn\">class</span><span class=\"pun\">=</span><span class=\"atv\">\"noposts\"</span><span class=\"tag\">&gt;</span>\r\n\r\n		    <span class=\"tag\">&lt;p&gt;</span><span class=\"pun\">&lt;?</span><span class=\"pln\">php _e</span><span class=\"pun\">(</span><span class=\"str\">\'None found.\'</span><span class=\"pun\">,</span><span class=\"str\">\'example\'</span><span class=\"pun\">);</span> <span class=\"pun\">?&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">&lt;/p&gt;</span>\r\n\r\n	    <span class=\"tag\">&lt;/div&gt;</span><span class=\"com\">&lt;!-- /#post-404 --&gt;</span>\r\n\r\n	<span class=\"pun\">&lt;?</span><span class=\"pln\">php endif</span><span class=\"pun\">;</span><span class=\"pln\"> wp_reset_query</span><span class=\"pun\">();</span> <span class=\"pun\">?&gt;</span>\r\n\r\n	<span class=\"tag\">&lt;/div&gt;</span><span class=\"com\">&lt;!-- /#content --&gt;</span>\r\n\r\n<span class=\"pun\">&lt;?</span><span class=\"pln\">php get_footer</span><span class=\"pun\">();</span> <span class=\"pun\">?&gt;</span></code></pre>\r\n</div>','Starting Quickly with Wordpress and going from there','','publish','open','closed','','starting-quickly-with-wordpress-and-going-from-there','','','2017-08-05 07:07:13','2017-08-05 07:07:13','',0,'http://www.localhost/fco/?p=495',0,'post','',0),(496,1,'2017-08-05 06:50:16','2017-08-05 06:50:16','','post-movingawayfromwordpress','','inherit','open','closed','','post-movingawayfromwordpress','','','2017-08-05 06:50:16','2017-08-05 06:50:16','',495,'http://www.localhost/fco/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/post-movingawayfromwordpress.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(497,1,'2017-08-05 06:50:36','2017-08-05 06:50:36','After you got everything all setup on your wordpress and your looking at the jumbled code wondering whats what. When will i grow  out of this website?: will all this work be all for naught? No ist wont. Steadilpy you can take your work page by page into your own code and move away from wordpress using the method shown below.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h1 class=\"entry-title\"><a title=\"Permanent Link to How to Build a Custom Page Template for Blog Posts\" href=\"https://upthemes.com/blog/2011/07/how-to-build-a-custom-page-template-for-blog-posts/\" rel=\"bookmark\">How to Build a Custom Page Template for Blog Posts</a></h1>\r\n<div class=\"entry-content\">\r\n<div id=\"essb_displayed_top_1454116323\" class=\"essb_links essb_displayed_top essb_share essb_template_flat-retina essb_1454116323 essb_links_center print-no\" data-essb-postid=\"1390\" data-essb-position=\"top\" data-essb-button-style=\"button\" data-essb-template=\"flat-retina\" data-essb-counter-pos=\"hidden\" data-essb-url=\"https://upthemes.com/blog/2011/07/how-to-build-a-custom-page-template-for-blog-posts/\" data-essb-twitter-url=\"https://upthemes.com/blog/2011/07/how-to-build-a-custom-page-template-for-blog-posts/\" data-essb-instance=\"1454116323\">\r\n<ul class=\"essb_links_list\">\r\n 	<li class=\"essb_item essb_link_twitter nolightbox\"><a title=\"\" href=\"https://upthemes.com/blog/2011/07/how-to-build-a-custom-page-template-for-blog-posts/#\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><span class=\"essb_network_name\">Twitter</span></a></li>\r\n 	<li class=\"essb_item essb_link_facebook nolightbox\"><a title=\"\" href=\"https://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=https://upthemes.com/blog/2011/07/how-to-build-a-custom-page-template-for-blog-posts/&amp;t=How+to+Build+a+Custom+Page+Template+for+Blog+Posts&amp;redirect_uri=https://upthemes.com?sharing-thankyou=yes\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><span class=\"essb_network_name\">Facebook</span></a></li>\r\n 	<li class=\"essb_item essb_link_google nolightbox\"><a title=\"\" href=\"https://plus.google.com/share?url=https://upthemes.com/blog/2011/07/how-to-build-a-custom-page-template-for-blog-posts/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><span class=\"essb_network_name\">Google+</span></a></li>\r\n 	<li class=\"essb_item essb_link_mwp nolightbox\"><a title=\"\" href=\"http://managewp.org/share/form?url=https%3A%2F%2Fupthemes.com%2Fblog%2F2011%2F07%2Fhow-to-build-a-custom-page-template-for-blog-posts%2F\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><span class=\"essb_network_name\">ManageWP.org</span></a></li>\r\n 	<li class=\"essb_item essb_link_pinterest nolightbox\"><a title=\"\" href=\"https://upthemes.com/blog/2011/07/how-to-build-a-custom-page-template-for-blog-posts/#\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><span class=\"essb_network_name\">Pinterest</span></a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\nWhen building out a custom “Blog” section for your WordPress site, sometimes it’s easiest to create a custom page template that you can customize that allows you to set the page location (such as https://upthemes.com/blog), as well as your very own title and description that are displayed at the top of the blog section.\r\n<h2>Step 1. Copy index.php to tpl_blog.php</h2>\r\nTo start, copy your index.php file from your current theme and rename the copied file tpl_blog.php. The reason for this is to get an exact copy of the theme functions and HTML structure from your current theme and to create a page template that will eventually be selectable from the ‘Page Template’ dropdown.\r\n<h2>Step 2. Create Page Template ID</h2>\r\nIn your new file tpl_blog.php, you need to add a special comment to the top of the file that WordPress will recognize as a custom template.\r\n<pre class=\"prettyprint prettyprinted\"><code lang=\"php\">\r\n<span class=\"com\">/*\r\nTemplate Name: Blog Posts\r\n*/</span></code></pre>\r\nSimply add that to the very top of your page and now WordPress will recognize it in the Edit Page screen sidebar.\r\n<h2>3. Use Custom Query for Posts</h2>\r\nPlace this below the get_header() template tag:\r\n<pre class=\"prettyprint prettyprinted\"><code lang=\"php\"><span class=\"pun\">&lt;?</span><span class=\"pln\">php query_posts</span><span class=\"pun\">(</span><span class=\"str\">\'post_type=post&amp;post_status=publish&amp;posts_per_page=10&amp;paged=\'</span><span class=\"pun\">.</span><span class=\"pln\"> get_query_var</span><span class=\"pun\">(</span><span class=\"str\">\'paged\'</span><span class=\"pun\">));</span> <span class=\"pun\">?&gt;</span></code></pre>\r\nThis will override the current page query with a custom query for 10 paginated blog posts. Since we’re using <code>query_posts()</code>, we don’t need to generate a new custom <code>WP_Query</code> to store the custom query.\r\n<h2>4. Add Navigational Links for Pagination</h2>\r\nBelow your post loop, add some links for pagination like so:\r\n<pre class=\"prettyprint prettyprinted\"><code lang=\"php\"><span class=\"tag\">&lt;div</span> <span class=\"atn\">class</span><span class=\"pun\">=</span><span class=\"atv\">\"navigation\"</span><span class=\"tag\">&gt;</span>\r\n	<span class=\"tag\">&lt;span</span> <span class=\"atn\">class</span><span class=\"pun\">=</span><span class=\"atv\">\"newer\"</span><span class=\"tag\">&gt;</span><span class=\"pun\">&lt;?</span><span class=\"pln\">php previous_posts_link</span><span class=\"pun\">(</span><span class=\"pln\">__</span><span class=\"pun\">(</span><span class=\"str\">\'« Newer\'</span><span class=\"pun\">,</span><span class=\"str\">\'example\'</span><span class=\"pun\">))</span> <span class=\"pun\">?&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">&lt;/span&gt;</span> <span class=\"tag\">&lt;span</span> <span class=\"atn\">class</span><span class=\"pun\">=</span><span class=\"atv\">\"older\"</span><span class=\"tag\">&gt;</span><span class=\"pun\">&lt;?</span><span class=\"pln\">php next_posts_link</span><span class=\"pun\">(</span><span class=\"pln\">__</span><span class=\"pun\">(</span><span class=\"str\">\'Older »\'</span><span class=\"pun\">,</span><span class=\"str\">\'example\'</span><span class=\"pun\">))</span> <span class=\"pun\">?&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">&lt;/span&gt;</span>\r\n<span class=\"tag\">&lt;/div&gt;</span><span class=\"com\">&lt;!-- /.navigation --&gt;</span></code></pre>\r\nThis should be between the <code>endwhile;</code> and <code>endif;</code> sections of code in your theme.\r\n<h2>5. Reset the Query</h2>\r\nOnce you’ve output all your posts and navigation, you can use <code>wp_reset_query()</code> to reset the <code>query_posts()</code> results that you created earlier. In lamens terms, you’ve now reset the query to what it was before you called <code>query_posts()</code>.\r\n<h2>6. Putting it all together</h2>\r\nHere’s a completed page template that utilizes everything described above with additional markup and includes the loop:\r\n<pre class=\"prettyprint prettyprinted\"><code lang=\"php\"><span class=\"tag\">&lt;php</span> <span class=\"atn\">get_header</span><span class=\"pln\">(); ?</span><span class=\"tag\">&gt;</span>\r\n\r\n	<span class=\"tag\">&lt;div</span> <span class=\"atn\">id</span><span class=\"pun\">=</span><span class=\"atv\">\"content\"</span><span class=\"tag\">&gt;</span>\r\n\r\n        <span class=\"pun\">&lt;?</span><span class=\"pln\">php query_posts</span><span class=\"pun\">(</span><span class=\"str\">\'post_type=post&amp;post_status=publish&amp;posts_per_page=10&amp;paged=\'</span><span class=\"pun\">.</span><span class=\"pln\"> get_query_var</span><span class=\"pun\">(</span><span class=\"str\">\'paged\'</span><span class=\"pun\">));</span> <span class=\"pun\">?&gt;</span>\r\n\r\n	<span class=\"pun\">&lt;?</span><span class=\"pln\">php </span><span class=\"kwd\">if</span><span class=\"pun\">(</span><span class=\"pln\"> have_posts</span><span class=\"pun\">()</span> <span class=\"pun\">):</span>