see that what is actually placed in git are the scripts needed to generate the initial database. There may be additional scripts, like those to populate the database data with a clean state, or to populate it with testing data. All such sql scripts are text files, and pretty much the same format as the sql dump you would get from mysqldump. So there\'s no reason you can\'t do it that way with your day-to-day data as well.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\nthen theres this wp plugin, which i will also try\n\nhttps://github.com/wp-sync-db/wp-sync-db\n\nI tried the wp sync. install and making it work took about an hour with everythign said and done. thats the first time i used a github wp plugin though. It wont work for our purposes as I realized that versioning the database will be crucial to working simultaneously in wordpress with someone other than myself.  It wont be crucial if they are just changing the javascript things though. Since this is easy, compressable, and now its installed I might choose this. option.\n\nI have also been tryign different file types to see if github is able to parse and make them versionable.... may have found the one. I saved the DB as CodeGen and a .cs file came out that looks incredibly promising. Turns out github was not able to detect the content changes. I tried php and .sql file types and it looks okay.  The diffs are the most detailed out of all the text files. Upon further testing i found that after i changed the file and replaced it and then did it agian. the .sql file updated correctly while the .phop file did not. Also it looks as though the .sql file was much more detailed in its diffs. The one redeemign quality about using .php was that the files are much more human readable. However, in the end .sql wins this battle as a definite contender in braindead ways to verision your DB and the great thing is it is still contained within GitHub no other platforms are needed so we are using githubs powerful diff ... next up are the final comabtants. Thoguh they deliver on their promises they require an expert to wield them.\n\n&nbsp;\n\nNOw there are these two compeeting (https://stackoverflow.com/questions/37385823/liquibase-vs-flyway-which-one-to-use) db migration tools: flyway(https://flywaydb.org/getstarted/download) and Liquibase(http://download.liquibase.org/)\n\nBoth use the command line and look like they require a certain degree of SQL knowledge, or other more involved knowledge sets to operate with any sort of confidence.','CMS WordPress DB Versioning and Syncing With GitHub: A \'how to\' on Continuous Deployment','','inherit','closed','closed','','498-autosave-v1','','','2017-08-08 06:41:48','2017-08-08 06:41:48','',498,'http://www.localhost/fco/498-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(506,1,'2017-08-08 00:12:27','2017-08-08 00:12:27','','coloring-pages-adults-zen-anti-stress-curves-tunels-and-hearts','','inherit','open','closed','','coloring-pages-adults-zen-anti-stress-curves-tunels-and-hearts-2','','','2017-08-08 00:12:27','2017-08-08 00:12:27','',0,'http://www.localhost/fco/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/coloring-pages-adults-zen-anti-stress-curves-tunels-and-hearts-1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(508,1,'2017-08-08 02:39:44','2017-08-08 02:39:44','Not well  documented but I think i have figured it out.... Only stack exchange offered manual answers, and there was a wp plugin. All other solutions are expensive as hell.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nobviously in 2010 it was still an issue\r\n\r\nfound this round about way on the way bottom of the discussion\r\n\r\nhttps://stackoverflow.com/questions/846659/how-can-i-put-a-database-under-git-version-control/28123546#28123546\r\n\r\ncool video though\r\n\r\nhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=c45AevIuYGk\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nin 2012 there was an answer, and one Im considering\r\n<h3 class=\"r\"><a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/13608706/using-version-control-git-on-a-mysql-database\">Using version control (Git) on a MySQL database 